-- Manchester United ‘Favorite’ to Sign Modric: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 2012-04-19T10:42:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-19/manchester-united-favorite-to-sign-modric-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of
soccer stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the
Web.  United Targets Modric, De Marcos  Manchester United  is targeting Tottenham Hotspur’s  Luka Modric , who is valued at 40 million pounds ($64 million), the
 Daily Star  reported. United is the “firm favorite” to sign the
midfielder this summer, ahead of Chelsea and Manchester City,
the newspaper said.  United is also trying to sign Athletic Bilbao midfielder
Oscar de Marcos, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  United manager Alex Ferguson is sending a scout to watch De
Marcos play against Sporting Lisbon in the first leg of the
Europa League semifinal tonight. De Marcos is valued at 26
million pounds.  Germans Chasing Dzeko  Bayern Munich  and Borussia Dortmund are chasing Manchester
City’s Edin Dzeko, the  Daily Mail  reported. City wants at least
20 million pounds for the Bosnian striker, the paper said.  Dempsey to Roma?  AS Roma may bid as much as 7 million pounds for Fulham top
scorer  Clint Dempsey  at the end of the season, the  Sun  reported.  The American, who has scored 16 goals this season, will be
out of contract in 2013. Arsenal is also interested in Dempsey,
the paper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
